{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The dismissal gate is the decision layer that sits between Claude's validation response and the alarm UI. When Claude returns "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "ValidationResponse"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", something must decide: dismiss now, ask the user to re-scan, or block dismissal entirely. That logic belongs in a pure, testable struct — not scattered across the view model. This section builds "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "DismissalGate"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " from scratch, wires it into the alarm view model, adds retry with backoff, and covers edge cases like force-dismiss and multi-attempt tracking."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Dismissal-gate architecture: alarm fires, Vision classifies, Claude validates, DismissalGate evaluates to allow/retry/deny"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "The DismissalDecision Enum" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before writing any gate logic, define its output as a typed enum. This forces every call site to handle all three outcomes explicitly, and keeps the branching behavior documented at the type level."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "enum DismissalDecision {\n    /// Claude says the scene is valid — dismiss the alarm.\n    case allow\n    /// Claude rejected the scene, but the user has attempts remaining — re-scan.\n    case retry(reason: String)\n    /// All attempts exhausted — block dismissal and surface a hard stop.\n    case deny(reason: String)\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Keep "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "DismissalDecision"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " separate from "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "ValidationResponse"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The former is a UI-level concept (what happens to the alarm); the latter is an API-level concept (what Claude returned). They evolve independently."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "The DismissalGate Struct" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The gate is a value type with no stored state. It takes a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "ValidationResponse"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the current attempt count, and the configured maximum, and returns a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "DismissalDecision"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Because it is pure, you can test every branch without any asynchronous setup."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "struct DismissalGate {\n    let maxAttempts: Int\n\n    init(maxAttempts: Int = 3) {\n        self.maxAttempts = maxAttempts\n    }\n\n    func evaluate(\n        response: ValidationResponse,\n        attempt: Int\n    ) -> DismissalDecision {\n        if response.valid {\n            return .allow\n        }\n        if attempt < maxAttempts {\n            return .retry(reason: response.reason)\n        }\n        return .deny(reason: response.reason)\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "attempt"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " parameter is 1-based: the first dismiss attempt is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "attempt: 1"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". When "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "attempt == maxAttempts"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and Claude still says invalid, the gate returns "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": ".deny"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Handling Low-Confidence Vision Results" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When Vision confidence is too low to call Claude at all (the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": ".skip"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " branch from "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "gateForClaude"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "), the alarm has no reliable scene data. The safest policy is to allow dismissal — you cannot meaningfully block when you have no signal. Log the skip reason so you can tune the confidence threshold later."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "func handleVisionSkip(reason: String) -> DismissalDecision {\n    // Log for threshold tuning; allow because blocking on no-signal harms UX.\n    print(\"[DismissalGate] Vision skipped: \\(reason)\")\n    return .allow\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Wiring Into the Alarm View Model" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The view model manages the mutable state (attempt count, UI feedback) while "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "DismissalGate"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " handles only the decision logic. This keeps the view model lean and the gate independently testable."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@MainActor\nfinal class AlarmViewModel: ObservableObject {\n    @Published var alarmActive = false\n    @Published var dismissalMessage: String?\n    @Published var isDismissing = false\n    @Published var forceDismissAvailable = false\n\n    private let classifier: ImageClassifierProtocol\n    private let validationService: ValidationServiceProtocol\n    private let gate = DismissalGate(maxAttempts: 3)\n    private var attempt = 0\n\n    init(\n        classifier: ImageClassifierProtocol,\n        validationService: ValidationServiceProtocol\n    ) {\n        self.classifier = classifier\n        self.validationService = validationService\n    }\n\n    func requestDismissal(image: UIImage, question: String) async {\n        guard alarmActive, !isDismissing else { return }\n        attempt += 1\n        isDismissing = true\n        defer { isDismissing = false }\n\n        do {\n            let labels = try await classifier.classify(image: image)\n            let decision: DismissalDecision\n\n            switch gateForClaude(labels: labels) {\n            case .skip(let reason):\n                decision = handleVisionSkip(reason: reason)\n            case .validate(let filtered):\n                let response = try await validationService.validate(\n                    labels: filtered,\n                    question: question\n                )\n                decision = gate.evaluate(response: response, attempt: attempt)\n            }\n\n            apply(decision: decision)\n        } catch {\n            // Network or decoding failure — allow dismissal rather than blocking.\n            apply(decision: .allow)\n        }\n    }\n\n    private func apply(decision: DismissalDecision) {\n        switch decision {\n        case .allow:\n            alarmActive = false\n            attempt = 0\n            forceDismissAvailable = false\n            dismissalMessage = nil\n        case .retry(let reason):\n            dismissalMessage = reason\n            forceDismissAvailable = false\n        case .deny(let reason):\n            dismissalMessage = reason\n            forceDismissAvailable = true\n        }\n    }\n\n    func forceDismiss() {\n        alarmActive = false\n        attempt = 0\n        forceDismissAvailable = false\n        dismissalMessage = nil\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Retry with Exponential Backoff" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the gate returns "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": ".retry"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the view tells the user to move to a clearer position and re-scan. Add a short delay before re-enabling the dismiss button so the user reads the reason before tapping again:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// In your SwiftUI view, after receiving .retry:\nTask {\n    let backoffSeconds: Double = attempt == 1 ? 1.0 : 2.0\n    try? await Task.sleep(for: .seconds(backoffSeconds))\n    // Re-enable the dismiss button — the user can try again.\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "One and two seconds are sufficient for a human to read feedback. Longer backoffs frustrate users during a genuine safety check. Don't use network-style exponential backoff (which can reach tens of seconds) — this is a UI interaction loop, not a retry against a rate-limited endpoint."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "The Force-Dismiss Escape Hatch" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": ".deny"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the alarm is still ringing. Always provide a force-dismiss path — Claude's judgment is a guide, not a lock. Surfacing it only after all attempts keeps the safety intent visible while respecting user autonomy."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "struct AlarmView: View {\n    @StateObject private var viewModel: AlarmViewModel\n\n    var body: some View {\n        VStack(spacing: 20) {\n            if let message = viewModel.dismissalMessage {\n                Text(message)\n                    .foregroundStyle(.secondary)\n                    .multilineTextAlignment(.center)\n                    .padding(.horizontal)\n            }\n\n            Button(\"Dismiss\") {\n                Task {\n                    await viewModel.requestDismissal(\n                        image: capturedImage,\n                        question: \"Is this a safe environment to dismiss the alarm?\"\n                    )\n                }\n            }\n            .disabled(viewModel.isDismissing)\n\n            if viewModel.forceDismissAvailable {\n                Button(\"Force Dismiss\", role: .destructive) {\n                    viewModel.forceDismiss()\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Resetting State Between Alarms" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The attempt counter must reset each time a new alarm fires. If you allow it to carry over, a user who struggled to dismiss a previous alarm starts the next one already at max attempts. Reset in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "alarmActive"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "'s didSet or in a dedicated "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "fireAlarm()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " function:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "func fireAlarm() {\n    attempt = 0\n    forceDismissAvailable = false\n    dismissalMessage = nil\n    alarmActive = true\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Logging Dismissal History" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Persisting a short history of recent dismissals lets you surface patterns (repeated force-dismissals may indicate a threshold that is too strict) and supports debugging. Write each outcome to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "UserDefaults"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or a lightweight SQLite store:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "struct DismissalRecord: Codable {\n    let date: Date\n    let outcome: String     // \"allow\", \"force\", \"deny\"\n    let reason: String?\n    let attemptCount: Int\n}\n\nfinal class DismissalHistory {\n    private let key = \"dismissalHistory\"\n    private let maxRecords = 50\n\n    func append(_ record: DismissalRecord) {\n        var history = load()\n        history.append(record)\n        if history.count > maxRecords { history.removeFirst(history.count - maxRecords) }\n        if let data = try? JSONEncoder().encode(history) {\n            UserDefaults.standard.set(data, forKey: key)\n        }\n    }\n\n    func load() -> [DismissalRecord] {\n        guard let data = UserDefaults.standard.data(forKey: key),\n              let records = try? JSONDecoder().decode([DismissalRecord].self, from: data)\n        else { return [] }\n        return records\n    }\n\n    var forceDismissRate: Double {\n        let history = load()\n        guard !history.isEmpty else { return 0 }\n        let forced = history.filter { $0.outcome == \"force\" }.count\n        return Double(forced) / Double(history.count)\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "If "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "forceDismissRate"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " exceeds ~20%, your thresholds or prompt are likely too strict for the real conditions users encounter."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Testing the Gate in Isolation" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Because "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "DismissalGate"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a pure struct, every branch is testable with zero async setup:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import XCTest\n\nfinal class DismissalGateTests: XCTestCase {\n    let gate = DismissalGate(maxAttempts: 3)\n\n    func testAllowsWhenValid() {\n        let response = ValidationResponse(valid: true, reason: \"Safe.\", advice: nil)\n        XCTAssertEqual(gate.evaluate(response: response, attempt: 1), .allow)\n    }\n\n    func testRetriesBeforeMax() {\n        let response = ValidationResponse(valid: false, reason: \"Unsafe area.\", advice: nil)\n        if case .retry(let reason) = gate.evaluate(response: response, attempt: 2) {\n            XCTAssertEqual(reason, \"Unsafe area.\")\n        } else {\n            XCTFail(\"Expected .retry\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    func testDeniesAtMax() {\n        let response = ValidationResponse(valid: false, reason: \"Blocked.\", advice: nil)\n        if case .deny(let reason) = gate.evaluate(response: response, attempt: 3) {\n            XCTAssertEqual(reason, \"Blocked.\")\n        } else {\n            XCTFail(\"Expected .deny\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    func testAllowsOnFirstAttemptValid() {\n        let response = ValidationResponse(valid: true, reason: \"OK.\", advice: nil)\n        XCTAssertEqual(gate.evaluate(response: response, attempt: 3), .allow)\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For testing the full view model flow, use a stub "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "ValidationServiceProtocol"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " that returns a predetermined "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "ValidationResponse"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The gate itself never needs to be mocked."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Configuring maxAttempts for Your App" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Three is a reasonable default for most alarm apps. Here is how different values trade off:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableHeader", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "maxAttempts" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableHeader", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "UX trade-off" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableHeader", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "When to use" }] }] }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "1" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Hard block on first failure; force-dismiss appears immediately" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "High-stakes alarms (medication, safety equipment)" }] }] }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "3" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Allows lighting/angle correction before blocking" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Most apps — balanced safety and UX" }] }] }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "5+" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Many retries; force-dismiss feels like an afterthought" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Low-stakes confirmation flows; not alarms" }] }] }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Common Pitfalls" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Forgetting to reset attempt on new alarm." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " The attempt counter bleeds across alarm invocations. Always call " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "fireAlarm()" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " to reset state when the alarm activates." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Blocking on API failure." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " If Claude is unreachable (network down, timeout, malformed JSON), the dismiss button is stuck. Always fall back to " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": ".allow" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " on unexpected errors — do not surface a \"cannot dismiss\" state due to infrastructure failure." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Comparing enum cases with == on associated value types." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "DismissalDecision" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " has associated values, so you can't use " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "==" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " unless you add " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "Equatable" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " conformance or use " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "if case" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " in tests." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Calling requestDismissal while already dismissing." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " A user can tap the dismiss button again before the async call returns. The " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "isDismissing" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " guard in " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "requestDismissal" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " prevents double-counting, but you must also disable the button in the UI." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Not surfacing Claude's advice." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "ValidationResponse.advice" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " often contains actionable guidance ('move to better lighting', 'step away from the hazard'). Showing it increases the chance the next scan succeeds." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Summary" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A dismissal gate decouples Claude's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
            "text": "ValidationResponse"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " from the alarm UI by mapping it to three typed outcomes: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }],
